{"id": "EUVD-2025-124908", "enisaUuid": "442fea06-e730-3c86-b18e-10df761724e2", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nidpf: cleanup remaining SKBs in PTP flows\n\nWhen the driver requests Tx timestamp value, one of the first steps is\nto clone SKB using skb_get. It increases the reference counter for that\nSKB to prevent unexpected freeing by another component.\nHowever, there may be a case where the index is requested, SKB is\nassigned and never consumed by PTP flows - for example due to reset during\nrunning PTP apps.\n\nAdd a check in release timestamping function to verify if the SKB\nassigned to Tx timestamp latch was freed, and release remaining SKBs.", "datePublished": "2025-11-12T10:53:50", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-01T06:19:30", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2c84e91ef831d4fedb0b94670b3cfd1cc5f966a5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a3f8c0a273120fd2638f03403e786c3de2382e72", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40175"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40175"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1ad3b3a6-4fdd-3a40-a0e0-1390585b7072", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.16"}, {"id": "2690ff6b-519f-341e-920b-889463e45fc0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "32a27764-6ce6-31f8-8871-9ca5c0a7fdd0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "5e23d799-bf38-3190-9316-0f9eab2123b9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4901e83a94ef0a8baf27916f31daf59b0a68547f <a3f8c0a273120fd2638f03403e786c3de2382e72"}, {"id": "620db786-7428-33b3-b024-d9206ab4d7ac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18-rc2"}, {"id": "6dd113c1-2f03-3885-839e-d37dcddea422", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4901e83a94ef0a8baf27916f31daf59b0a68547f <2c84e91ef831d4fedb0b94670b3cfd1cc5f966a5"}, {"id": "8f8e0cc9-6866-3f61-9443-c0aeb8d27a76", "product": {"name": "Linux"}